    },
    {
      "text": "Japan is divided into 47 administrative prefectures and eight traditional regions, and around 75% of its terrain is mountainous and heavily forested, concentrating its agriculture and highly urbanized population along its eastern coastal plains.",
      "source_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan",
      "source_type": "reference_work",
      "confidence_tier": "reported",
